verses.verse_html: 1Elihu spake moreover, and said,

verses.text_plain: Thinkest thou this to be right, that thou saidst, My righteousness is more than God’s?
verses.verse_html: 2Thinkest thou this to be right, that thou saidst, My righteousness is more than God’s?

verses.text_plain: For thou saidst, What advantage will it be unto thee? and, What profit shall I have, if I be cleansed from my sin?
verses.verse_html:
3For thou saidst, What advantage will it be unto thee? and, What profit shall I have, if I be cleansed from my sin? ▼
▼ if…: or, by it more than by my sin

footnotes.body_text: ▼ if…: or, by it more than by my sin
footnotes.body_html: ▼ if…: or, by it more than by my sin

verses.text_plain: I will answer thee, and thy companions with thee.
verses.verse_html:
4I will answer thee, and thy companions with thee. ▼
▼ answer…: Heb. return to thee words

footnotes.body_text: ▼ answer…: Heb. return to thee words
footnotes.body_html: ▼ answer…: Heb. return to thee words

verses.text_plain: Look unto the heavens, and see; and behold the clouds which are higher than thou.
verses.verse_html: 5Look unto the heavens, and see; and behold the clouds which are higher than thou.

verses.text_plain: If thou sinnest, what doest thou against him? or if thy transgressions be multiplied, what doest thou unto him?
verses.verse_html: 6If thou sinnest, what doest thou against him? or if thy transgressions be multiplied, what doest thou unto him?

verses.text_plain: If thou be righteous, what givest thou him? or what receiveth he of thine hand?
verses.verse_html: 7If thou be righteous, what givest thou him? or what receiveth he of thine hand?

verses.text_plain: Thy wickedness may hurt a man as thou art; and thy righteousness may profit the son of man.
verses.verse_html: 8Thy wickedness may hurt a man as thou art; and thy righteousness may profit the son of man.

verses.text_plain: By reason of the multitude of oppressions they make the oppressed to cry: they cry out by reason of the arm of the mighty.
verses.verse_html: 9By reason of the multitude of oppressions they make the oppressed to cry: they cry out by reason of the arm of the mighty.

verses.text_plain: But none saith, Where is God my maker, who giveth songs in the night;
verses.verse_html: 10But none saith, Where is God my maker, who giveth songs in the night;

verses.text_plain: Who teacheth us more than the beasts of the earth, and maketh us wiser than the fowls of heaven?
verses.verse_html: 11Who teacheth us more than the beasts of the earth, and maketh us wiser than the fowls of heaven?

verses.text_plain: There they cry, but none giveth answer, because of the pride of evil men.
verses.verse_html: 12There they cry, but none giveth answer, because of the pride of evil men.

verses.text_plain: Surely God will not hear vanity, neither will the Almighty regard it.
verses.verse_html: 13Surely God will not hear vanity, neither will the Almighty regard it.

verses.text_plain: Although thou sayest thou shalt not see him, yet judgment is before him; therefore trust thou in him.
verses.verse_html: 14Although thou sayest thou shalt not see him, yet judgment is before him; therefore trust thou in him.

verses.text_plain: But now, because it is not so, he hath visited in his anger; yet he knoweth it not in great extremity:
verses.verse_html:
15But now, because it is not so, he hath visited in his anger; yet he knoweth it not in great extremity: ▼
▼ he hath: that is, God hath
 , ▼
▼ he knoweth: that is, Job knoweth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ he hath: that is, God hath
footnotes.body_html: ▼ he hath: that is, God hath

footnotes.body_text: ▼ he knoweth: that is, Job knoweth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ he knoweth: that is, Job knoweth

verses.text_plain: Therefore doth Job open his mouth in vain; he multiplieth words without knowledge.
verses.verse_html: 16Therefore doth Job open his mouth in vain; he multiplieth words without knowledge.
